values: So this past weekend with my roommate in tow we decided to go to New York, however in the process we ended up going to ten different states...NC,VA,MD,NJ,DE,NY,MA,RI,CT,and PA to round it all out.  Who knew that I-95 South ran less than 5 miles off the border of PA, well my roommate being the amazing person that she is managed to navigate us to PA without any problem.  I bought the map months ago and finally looked at them after being lost trying to get to Boston, who knew.  It was awesome just the same, but I was so happy to be on the road back.  NYC and Boston are so not pretty no trees, drab buildings, scary people, and the cops don't like me, anywho that's another entry...I'm happy to be back though class awaits...ttyl

So I'm feeling fine...talking to Heidi, then Beth (whoa! its not just a crush anymore Beth)...and I'm all excited, then I go outside to go with the ATH people to see Lost In Translation (don't go see it its horrible) and my throat starts hurting, so I'm ignoring it then half way through the movie my ears start hurting then I'm like I'm taking a nap...yep right in the middle of the movie I'm totally asleep (I'm afraid I might turn into my grandma) then I'm all feeling bad so I skip the sleepover and come back to the room to medicine it up and conk out on the bed...so i'm basically half sleep/half awake/and very sleepy...ttyl

So we've been snowed and iced in for the past 2 days and its been gloriously boring, although I don't necessarily want to go to class tomorrow the activity will break the tedium.  On another note, have you ever been totally and completely infatuated with someone...it is utterly and completely unhealthy...I had the weirdest dream about her again...this is just odd because I never get infatuations...I'm always the practical one with the solutions...anywho I have class tomorrow so nitey nite

I'm going insane I'm having a nervous breakdown...nah i'm really not, but the last couple of weeks for me have been totally insane and abnormal...hopefully things'll get back on track next week...everything will just even itself out...ttyl

I am now in love with ATH the people are good and the dorm is nice.  For those who don't know its a selective house that you pledge at my school called the arts theme house.  It turns out there are people very similar to me just as wild and insane.  Plus they have a clue thank goodness.  No more weird middle of the night disturbances out of rudeness.  headaches finally gone thank goodness that's all folks.

Someone should revoke my online access cause I keep getting these weird messages and ims from random people...I am like removing my personals no more messages for or from me this is sooo insane.  I g2g to bed now this day has truly been intensely tiring...nighty night Beth.

This was by far the best and most useful MLK day I have ever had I went to a program called "move on up a little higher:sermons and songs" at my school and it celebrated mlk and mahalia jackson and it was sooo awesome.  it was like you got to go to church and hear the two then later on you got to see these multicultural presentations from African and South American origin.  Then one of the school choirs decided to show off and it was awesome I had no clue they were good...holla at you Kori and Bianca.  I got to reconnect with my Aamp which means i now have a ride to see Barbershop 2 and can make some Greek Life connects(they have the best parties.)  Then Talib Kweli who originally came out with Mos Def came and started a discussion on race, religion, etc.  Most Importantly he preached activism it was soo refreshing to see a rapper who is conscientious and not talking about bitches, hoes, and diamonds.  He actually knew why people should not be rapping about those things and the fact that Africans are being killed for them.  It was just a great day then the person I like called it is truly awesome mega.

Some female that I have never met locates my profile on some website e-mails me and says she wants to have sex with me and I'm like who the hell are you...we're having lunch next week...I turned all of my paperwork for study abroad...i sold my laptop for a $300, so I'm going to use that as a down payment for a car...I was really sick earlier this week I mean really sick I missed class and everything...i've decided i don't need to play poker with my friends anymore, because it breeds negative vibes...I got a new job at Cutco of all places weird I know...I start training Thursday and I'll figure everything else out later...I saw the most horrible play ever today called Pippin it was a 2 and a half out of 10 because a friend and a cute kid were in the play...must cheer on the eagles now...later
All I have to say is thank God the bed is so near...it was just a really bad day...nite

The day started pretty hectic...I woke up 30 minutes after I was supposed to be at work...I rushed to mail off my mom's birthday present and turn in my major paperwork to the pre major center...I turned it in and on 2-6-04 I will officially have a major and a permanent tract...exciting...then I got to work exactly an hour after I was supposed to get there...then the damn computers weren't working so I just sat there bored out of my mind...I get off at 2 run to class and get utterly confused when my HISTORY professor tried to explain newtonian and materialism physics...I'm science illiterate so I don'tknow what the hell he was saying...its like myy brain just turned off...he started saying force equals gravity times this other stuff and I'm trying to figure out why we're trying to define physics in a history class...then I rush back to work and convince my boss to let me have a break at 4;30 so I can go to a study abroad meeting for Switzerland...I'll be able to see the French and Swiss Alps maybe even snowboard them...I'm so in love...its my first choice now, but I had to leave early to run back to work...I left at 7 then ran around the library trying to find some books for class...I'm too cheap to buy them...I had to go to all 4 floors and at least 2 doors on each floor...this place is huge and what's more amazing is that the campus has 2 big libraries and like 6 smaller libraries...its freaking humongous...i get back to my dorm and my roommate calls and asks me to play poker I say yes...we played for 2 hours before a person was eliminated it was sooo long...I was not the first to get out and i had the lowest amount of chips several times...I'm finally getting ready for bed I was beginning to think this was never gonna happen today...so night...

I actually woke up early enough to eat brunch today, then I went to the women's basketball game vs. UNC...it was probably the most intense and wonderful sporting event I have ever attended...it was so awesome...I was in pain because I hurt my foot wrestling with Andrew last night (he dissed the titans in front of me) I could not let it pass...so everytime i got excited and wated to jump up and down, shooting pains shot up my leg from my foot...it was soooo painful, but I couldn't help it...Duke for life, and I so love women's basketball it is truly the way basketball is to be played without the impurities that are seen in the male version of the sport...we won by the way  we reared back in the last 5 minutes to push forward to a lead and kept scoring, ending with a 22 point difference...we were awesome and that Ivory chivk got schooled by her elder Alana...it was so beautiful...by the way I really don't like UNC they seriously got on my nerves with the harassment...but now I'm popping a couple of pain pills and napping in the middle of the day...life is truly beautiful roberto benigni (however you spell his name) :-)

I would say I'm marijuana, but I do take showers....don't watch that 70s show...depends on who's on the couch with me on the staying in part...oh and i so love chocolate...:)

Laid back, dreamy, and maybe a little stinky from skipping a shower.
You rather hang out on the couch watching That 70s Show than go clubbing.
All you need is a big joint, TV, and some Twinkies covered in chocolate syrup!

My roommate and I have way too much in common, it's getting really freaky...we both like the same things...we are usually the only people who understands what the other is trying to say...we don't sleep...we've both been blind in our life (no joke)...we're both clumsy...we both have relatives who have birthdays next Friday...and we're just weird...she is the white Russian version of me....its uncanny...apparently the housing people are good at their jobs...thank you oh housing gods...anyway its party night so inebriation will come a bit later...good day indeed...I even got my mommy a present for her 40th birthday next Friday...our mother's are the same age too...its a wonderful tennis bracelet cost a bit more than I wanted to pay but very worth it...I must go now...partay :)

So my advisor signed off on my major declaration, now the history people and polisci people have to do so too...I'm 2 steps away from being on an actual path to graduation...Decided that I'm going to do study abroad this summer...now the question is ghana, oxford, or switzerland...never been to either...it'd be a hard choice...anyway have to go shopping for food then poker for the rest of the night.

I attended 3 classes today and found out 2 would not have exams...awesome...but the other is probably the most boring I've ever had and it includes music which I normally love...Guess I'll just have to change, because I can't sleep through class everyday as I did today...any suggestions?

Free at last, free at last...I'm finally home to the wonderful environment of duke...it welcomes me with open arms, enveloping me in creative and emotional love, I have found a mate, nonsexual but intellectually, I have found my match...plus I have 6 or 7 crazy friends who actually know what the hell I'm trying to say when I attempt it...It's wonderful to be understood too bad it took 18 years, but joy at last...catch you on the flip side :)
I'm packing because tomorrow at 12:00 I leave for Durham...I am so excited...I missed it soo much...I missed all of my friends....I love you all...see ya tomorrow...be safe on your way back everyone

It's been 2004 for 11 hours, and there has already been drama...of course it doesn't necessarily affect me in a negative way...one of my friends woke up this morning in someone's house that she has never been to or seen before...instead of grabbing her stuff  and going out the front door...she gets everything and goes out the bedroom window...she slips and falls right on her ass in a very disgusting mud puddle or whatever...so she's like covered with mud and she's trying to put on her clothes and walk away from the mysterious lady's house at the same time...she literally hops around the block to the nearest gas station, where she attempts to call a cab on a payphone, but she has no change...so she calls me...I get there like 30 minutes later...and she's ripe, dirty, and crying...so I go was she hot?...and she gets totally pissed...was it really that bad of a joke...anyway I take her back to her place hold her hand while she pukes the whole nine...This whole fiasco has helped me make one more new year's resolution...if i drink to get drunk it will be done in my home...my promise to myself...

Happy new year everyone...my mommy's home...so all is well in the household...my friends kidnapped me yesterday and forced me to go to the club and dance and have fun...Thank you Ashley and Megan your the best friends a girl could have...And to that special someone you know who you are thanks for the ride...Love you lots...Everyone I hope you make resolutions and keep them...I've given up myself...But let's try this one...Be happier next year than I have ever been before...simple...my middle name...

Ok, so I'm watching the movie Seabiscuit for the second time...because the first time it put me to sleep....everything's cool til I realize how ridiculously made this movie truly is in comparison to the book...for any and all who might be trying to determine if its worthwhile to rent...it is but read the book instead...the intellectual stimulation will be much better than the brain damage resulting from watching an epic movie that isn't quite up the snuff...and Tobey Maguire is super short...I might even be able to look him straight in the eyes without heels that is sooo bad...That's my enlightening thought for the day, so think about it and read more...it's good for your brain.
